sequenceDiagram
    %% End-to-end planner sequences:
    %%   1. Console enqueue + Worker submission tick - happy path
    %%   2. Reservation-expiry sweeper - submitted -> superseded; new attempt inserted
    %%
    %% Cancellation is NOT a planner-driven flow: the OpenAI Batches API
    %% exposes /cancel on MDS, and any user-facing cancel travels through
    %% MDS directly. The planner observes the resulting MDS terminal state
    %% on its read-time overlay (Planner.GetJob / ListJobs) and surfaces
    %% it via JobView.LifecycleState - see the README "JobLifecycleState"
    %% derivation table.

    participant UI as Console UI
    participant BFF as Console BFF
    participant P as Planner
    participant TS as TaskStore
    participant W as Worker
    participant RM as RM
    participant BC as BatchClient
    participant MDS

    Note over UI,MDS: 1. Enqueue and Worker submission

    UI->>BFF: CreateJob
    BFF->>P: Enqueue PlannerJob
    P->>TS: write PlannerTask Attempt=1 state queued
    TS-->>P: ok
    P-->>BFF: EnqueueResult queued
    BFF-->>UI: JobID status queued

    Note over W: dispatcher tick - single process<br/>one dispatcher + N task goroutines

    W->>TS: Claim N tasks for FCFS<br/>or ListCandidates + SchedulerFunc + ClaimByID for custom policy
    TS-->>W: claimed tasks state claimed

    W->>RM: acquire capacity for TaskID + ResourceRequirement
    alt insufficient resources
        RM-->>W: error wrapped as ErrInsufficientResources
        W->>TS: Nack with backoff
    else success
        RM-->>W: RM-side response<br/>worker translates into Reservation<br/>ID, Allocations, ExpiresAt
        Note over W: idempotent per TaskID<br/>a re-claiming worker after crash gets the same handle back
    end

    Note over W: Worker.submit private method<br/>build MDSBatchSubmission from task + Reservation
    W->>BC: GetBatch by aibrix.job_id - pre-submit dedup
    alt batch already exists
        BC-->>W: existing BatchStatus
        Note over W: short-circuit - Ack with existing BatchID
    else not found
        BC-->>W: not found
        W->>BC: CreateBatch with MDSBatchSubmission
        BC->>MDS: POST v1 batches with extra_body aibrix
        MDS-->>BC: Batch
        BC-->>W: BatchStatus with BatchID
    end

    W->>TS: Ack TaskID BatchID ReservationID ReservationExpiresAt
    Note over W,RM: Reservation NOT released here<br/>held past submit so the sweeper can detect<br/>reservation expired before MDS finished<br/>release happens on Fail, post-MaxAttempts Nack,<br/>or observed MDS-terminal

    Note over P,MDS: 2. Reservation-expiry sweep - planner-internal background

    Note over RM,MDS: RM-side expiry tears down GPU pods<br/>MDS marks its batch failed or expired on its own<br/>planner does NOT release capacity here

    loop every sweep tick
        P->>TS: ListSubmittedWithExpiringReservation before now
        TS-->>P: candidate PlannerTasks - each is one attempt

        loop for each candidate
            P->>TS: EnqueueContinuation supersededTaskID newTask
            Note over TS: atomic - prior to superseded, BatchID kept for audit<br/>new task inserted - Attempt+1, state queued, fresh TaskID<br/>fresh TaskID forces a fresh RM-side capacity allocation
            TS-->>P: ok
        end
    end
